      "message": "Returning `qi`iterator without pointing to the first element seems be more reasonable. It\u0027s more consistent operations for users. They could always follow the pattern `qi.next(); qi.currentItem()`. Otherwise, users need to call `qi.currentItem()` for first item and use `qi.next(); qi.currentItem()` for the rest items. \n\nThe raw db seems to use the same pattern by calling `next()` to get the first element and check if it\u0027s Stop. - https://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/master:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/gae/impl/prod/raw_datastore.go;l\u003d272-275",
